[% META title = 'Comserv Development Plans' %]

<div class="documentation-content">

<h1>Comserv Development Plans</h1>

<p>This document serves as an index for all ongoing and planned development initiatives for the Comserv application.</p>

<h2>Current Initiatives</h2>

<div class="initiative">
    <h3>1. Documentation System Improvements</h3>

    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> In Progress</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> High</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> Development Team</p>
        <p><strong>Project Code:</strong> DOC-ROLE-001</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> <a href="[% c.uri_for('/Documentation/DocumentationRoleAccess') %]">Documentation Role Access</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Improve the documentation system with proper role-based visibility filtering. Unauthenticated users see only login/getting-started docs. Normal users see user-level docs. Editors, developers, admins, and CSC admins see progressively more. Improve the META block scanner to accurately sort documents into correct categories. Add an admin UI for assigning roles to individual documents. Site name and username filtering improvements.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="initiative-progress">
        <p><strong>Progress:</strong></p>
        <ul class="task-list">
            <li class="completed">✅ Initial role-based filtering infrastructure in place</li>
            <li class="completed">✅ META block parsing in ScanMethods.pm</li>
            <li class="completed">✅ DocumentationConfig.json category/role configuration</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Improve unauthenticated (guest) user filtering — limited to login/getting-started only</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Ensure CSC admin role maps to full access</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Fix meta block scanning for accurate initial document categorisation</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Admin UI for assigning roles per document</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ SiteName and username filtering improvements</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Consider DB migration using the Pages system for display</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="initiative">
    <h3>2. Controller Routing Standardization</h3>
    
    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> In Progress</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> High</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> Development Team</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> <a href="[% c.uri_for('/documentation/controller_routing_standardization') %]">Controller Routing Standardization</a></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Standardizing controller routing across the application using Catalyst's chained actions for better organization, maintainability, and scalability.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-progress">
        <p><strong>Progress:</strong></p>
        <ul class="task-list">
            <li class="completed">✅ MCoop controller updated as pilot implementation</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Update high-traffic controllers (CSC, USBM, BMaster)</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Update remaining controllers</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Add automated tests to verify routing functionality</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="initiative">
    <h3>2. Software Management System Enhancements</h3>
    
    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Planned</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> High</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> Development Team</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> <a href="[% c.uri_for('/documentation/software_management_system') %]">Software Management System</a></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Enhancing the existing software management system with improved error handling, automated backups, rollback capabilities, and advanced deployment features.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-progress">
        <p><strong>Planned Tasks:</strong></p>
        <ul class="task-list">
            <li class="pending">⬜ Enhanced error handling and recovery mechanisms</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Automated backup system with configurable retention</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ One-click rollback functionality</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Dependency management integration</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Pre-deployment validation and testing</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Advanced deployment strategies (blue-green, canary)</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Monitoring and alerting improvements</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Integration with CI/CD pipelines</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Database migration management</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Configuration management and validation</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="initiative">
    <h3>4. Theme Handling Improvements</h3>
    
    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Planned</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> Medium</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> TBD</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> TBD</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Improving theme handling to ensure consistent theme application across the application, including updating theme_mappings.json to use consistent case for site names.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-progress">
        <p><strong>Planned Tasks:</strong></p>
        <ul class="task-list">
            <li class="pending">⬜ Audit current theme handling across controllers</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Update theme_mappings.json for consistent case</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Centralize theme handling logic</li>
            <li class="pending">⬜ Add theme validation and error handling</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<h2>Completed Initiatives</h2>

<div class="initiative completed">
    <h3>1. MCoop Controller Fix</h3>
    
    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Completed</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> High</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> Development Team</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> <a href="[% c.uri_for('/documentation/mcoop_controller_fix') %]">MCoop Controller Fix</a></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Fixed site name case handling and routing in the MCoop controller, implementing chained routing as a pilot for the Controller Routing Standardization initiative.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-progress">
        <p><strong>Completed Tasks:</strong></p>
        <ul class="task-list">
            <li class="completed">✅ Fixed site name case handling</li>
            <li class="completed">✅ Implemented chained routing</li>
            <li class="completed">✅ Removed redundant SiteName setting</li>
            <li class="completed">✅ Added backward compatibility methods</li>
            <li class="completed">✅ Documented changes and standardization plan</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<h2>Planned Future Initiatives</h2>

<div class="initiative future">
    <h3>1. API Standardization</h3>
    
    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Planned</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> Medium</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> TBD</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> TBD</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Standardizing API endpoints and response formats across the application for better integration with frontend and third-party systems.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="initiative future">
    <h3>2. Performance Optimization</h3>
    
    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Planned</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> Medium</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> TBD</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> TBD</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Identifying and addressing performance bottlenecks in the application, including database queries, template rendering, and API calls.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="initiative future">
    <h3>3. Security Enhancements</h3>
    
    <div class="initiative-meta">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Planned</p>
        <p><strong>Priority:</strong> High</p>
        <p><strong>Lead:</strong> TBD</p>
        <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> TBD</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="initiative-description">
        <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
        Enhancing security measures across the application, including input validation, authentication, authorization, and data protection.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<h2>How to Contribute</h2>

<p>If you would like to contribute to any of these initiatives or propose a new one, please follow these steps:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Review the existing documentation for the initiative</li>
    <li>Discuss your ideas with the development team</li>
    <li>Create a detailed proposal for your contribution</li>
    <li>Submit a pull request with your changes</li>
</ol>

<h2>Initiative Template</h2>

<p>When proposing a new initiative, please use the following template:</p>

<div class="template-example">
    <h4>Initiative Name</h4>
    
    <p><strong>Status:</strong> [Planned/In Progress/Completed]<br>
    <strong>Priority:</strong> [Low/Medium/High]<br>
    <strong>Lead:</strong> [Name or Team]<br>
    <strong>Documentation:</strong> [Link to Documentation]</p>
    
    <p><strong>Description:</strong><br>
    [Brief description of the initiative]</p>
    
    <p><strong>Tasks:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>⬜ [Task 1]</li>
        <li>⬜ [Task 2]</li>
        <li>⬜ [Task 3]</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p><strong>Success Criteria:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>[Criterion 1]</li>
        <li>[Criterion 2]</li>
        <li>[Criterion 3]</li>
    </ul>
</div>

</div>

<style>
